Hey Stan, I suspect your "hot cam" whatever that grind is, is your reason
for the dead spot. Generally, the valve clearance, unless under .004, will
have no effect on hesitation. 

You are right about the bug DP engines getting the looser valve clearance on
the California carbureted models, then in 74 with all fuel injected. I still
have no problems with .006, since the CA pollution requirements are the
least of my worries.

